CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 21, 1956, pg. 17, reads: "At Flamingo - The versatile Bobby Jones Trio moved into its third smash week at the Flamingo Hotel, much to the pleasure of lovers of good music. The finely coordinated unit plays everything from rock and roll to melodious popular tunes.  Left to right: Toby Lyons, drums; Bobby, piano and vocal, and Bobby Boswell, bass. - Advt."
TitMainTitle: Toby Lyons on drums, Bobby Jones on piano, and Bobby Boswell on bass, in Flamingo Club
